      • TYPE_EXPORT_SINGLE_OUTPUT

        public static final String TYPE_EXPORT_SINGLE_OUTPUT
        Whether or not all export output is handled as a single unit or as a distributed set of units. The behavior is as follows:
        • If true, then all export records are funneled through a single record writer.
        • If false, then all export records are delivered to one or more record writers.
        A false value will result in higher performance but will also result in multiple record writers being created, each going to a separate output. In general, the record writers will utilize more of the cluster's worker nodes.

        A true value will result in exactly one cluster node with exactly one record writer.

        For example, sinks that write to file systems may want to use true so that all output is placed into a single exported file.

        A counter example is be an Accumulo based sink, which is not concerned with the number of output writers and would be more efficient if false is used.
